author: Gary Drapcho
title: Sanders Leads Lakers Past Edinboro
text:
Sanders Leads Lakers Past Edinboro   
Reggie Sanders ran for 170 yards and two touchdown to lead the Lakers to a 38-28 comeback win over Edinboro Thursday night. The Scots jumped on top 14-0 in the first quarter getting a 47 yd punt return TD from Mitch Thomas and a 2 yd TD run from Cory Bell but the Lakers came back with a touchdown pass and TD run from Lakers QB Zack Emerick. Sanders sealed the game in the second half two touchdowns including a 75 yard run. Edinboro drops to 0-8 while the Lakers end their losing skid at 4 in a row and improve to 4-4 on the season.
